# Geoapify API key — enables English-labeled map tiles on the country pages.
# Get one free at https://www.geoapify.com/ (free tier: 3,000 tiles/day).
# Copy this file to ".env" and paste your key below.
#
# Without a key, the embedded country maps fall back to OpenStreetMap tiles,
# which render place names in each region's local language.
#
# This is read by Vite at BUILD time (note the required VITE_ prefix) and baked
# into the static bundle. For Docker builds, pass it through as a build arg —
# the compose files forward ${VITE_GEOAPIFY_KEY} from the host environment.
VITE_GEOAPIFY_KEY=
